          "version": "7.7",
          "input_ue_unconnectable": {}
        }
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "IAMCCS Exec Planner - Quick Start\n\nUse this node for audio-driven generations.\n\n1. Choose Pipeline Family:\n- modern pipeline: recommended default.\n- legacy exact pipeline: alternate older route; useful for comparison or when it gives better motion/lipsync.\n\n2. Choose Pipeline Shape:\n- single generation: first test and shortest setup.\n- 2 segments: recommended first segmented test.\n- 3 segments: longer controlled generation.\n- loop / 4+ segments: long audio or songs.\n\n3. Timing:\n- FPS is passed to Render and VAE through LINX.\n- single generation uses Duration (s).\n- segmented routes use Segments or Seconds / Segment.\n- Overlap Frames default: 9. Try 12-17 only if the join is too abrupt.\n\n4. Audio Mode:\n- melband_vocals_duration_math: best for speech/singing lipsync.\n- raw_audio_only: keeps full audio/music; useful for music videos, but lipsync may follow instruments if vocals are not isolated.\n\ntext+audio2video uses single generation.\nFinal audio is passed as raw/full audio through Exec VAE audio_passthrough.\n\nCode by Carmine Cristallo Scalzi AI research (IAMCCS) patreon.com/IAMCCS"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
