      "title": "Exec VAE - instructions",
      "properties": {
        "ue_properties": {
          "widget_ue_connectable": {},
          "version": "7.7",
          "input_ue_unconnectable": {}
        }
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "IAMCCS Exec VAE - Quick Start\n\nChoose output/decode mode here.\n\nVAE Mode:\n- normal_tiled_iamccs: recommended default and best first test.\n- high_vram: faster/direct decode if you have enough VRAM.\n- low_ram: slower disk-assisted route.\n- very_low_ram: slowest/safest low-memory route.\n\nFor segmented/loop generations:\n- normal/high usually keep the normal route.\n- low/very_low use disk decode. In the log you should see low_ram_disk or very_low_ram_disk.\n\nOutput:\n- Frame Rate should match the Planner FPS.\n- CRF 18-20 is a good quality range.\n- trim_to_audio can be enabled if the final video must end exactly with the audio.\n- Final audio should come from LINX/audio_passthrough.\n\n\nCode by Carmine Cristallo Scalzi AI research (IAMCCS) patreon.com/IAMCCS"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    }
